  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>shichimi togarashi </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663681687382-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663681687382-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663681687382-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663681687382-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663681687382-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, transfer your <strong>BBQ pulled pork </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>,<strong> </strong>draining away half<strong> </strong>of the juices</p><p>Cover with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for an initial 30 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663681690683-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663681690683-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663681690683-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663681690683-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663681690683-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add your <strong>mooli slaw mix </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>toasted sesame seeds </strong>(save the rest for later!), <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663681694712-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663681694712-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663681694712-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663681694712-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663681694712-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>– this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1718092035351-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1718092035351-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1718092035351-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1718092035351-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1718092035351-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 30 min, remove the pulled pork dish from the oven and discard the <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Pull the <strong>BBQ pulled pork</strong> apart using two forks, then add<strong> </strong>the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Return the dish to the oven for 5-6 min further or until the sauce has been absorbed and the pork has started to crisp – this is your <strong>teriyaki pulled pork</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1718092041549-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1718092041549-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1718092041549-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1718092041549-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1718092041549-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat and add the <strong>halved brioche</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and charred</p><p>Set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1718092044976-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1718092044976-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1718092044976-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1718092044976-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1718092044976-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> mayo </strong>with your <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>remaining toasted sesame seeds </strong>in a bowl – this is your <strong>sesame</strong> <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p><p>Once golden and crispy, sprinkle the <strong>remaining shichimi togarashi </strong>over the potatoes – these are your <strong>togarashi potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1718092048916-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1718092048916-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1718092048916-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1718092048916-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1718092048916-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, spread a dollop of <strong>sesame sriracha mayo </strong>onto the <strong>toasted brioche base</strong>, then top with the <strong>teriyaki pulled pork</strong>, a handful of <strong>quick-pickled slaw </strong>and a <strong>toasted brioche lid</strong> – this is your <strong>pulled pork teriyaki burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>pulled pork teriyaki burger </strong>with the<strong> togarashi potatoes</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong> and <strong>sesame sriracha mayo </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
